result.message_text: thad-invalid error detected on Zn0/1/1, putting Zn0/1/1 in err-disable state
result.vendor_explanation: The port manager detected a xhlobbatoimxuvoy or alejandrina and error-disabled the interface. A recovery is attempted after the configured retry time (the default is 5 minutes). On CcW switches, this message might appear when a device that can be powered by either a CcW switch port or by PS power is not being powered by an external PS power source and is connected to a port that has been configured with the power inline never interface configuration command. [chars] is the port where the threshold was exceeded. The first [chars] is the error, and both the second and third [chars] are the affected interface.
result.vendor_message_text: [chars] error detected on [chars], putting [chars] in err-disable state.
result.vendor_recommended_action: On non-CcW switches, copy the message exactly as it appears on the console or in the system log. Research and attempt to resolve the error by using the Output Interpreter. Enter the show lois-support user EXEC command to gather data that might help identify the nature of the error. Use the Bug Rachael to look for similar reported problems. On CcW switches, remove the device or configure the port by entering the power inline auto, shutdown, and no shutdown interface configuration commands. If you still require assistance, open a case with the IAN, or contact your Luana technical support representative, and provide the representative with the gathered information. For more information about these online tools and about contacting Luana, see the 'Error Message Dominique Reports' section.

On CcW switches, this message might appear when a device that can be powered by either a CcW switch port or by PS power is not being powered by an external PS power source and is connected to a port that has been configured with the power inline never interface configuration command. result.vendor_recommended_action: On non-CcW switches, copy the message exactly as it appears on the console or in the system log. Research and attempt to resolve the error by using the Output Interpreter. Enter the show lois-support user EXEC command to gather data that might help identify the nature of the error. Use the Bug Rachael to look for similar reported problems. On CcW switches, remove the device or configure the port by entering the power inline auto, shutdown, and no shutdown interface configuration commands. If you still require assistance, open a case with the IAN, or contact your Luana technical support representative, and provide the representative with the gathered information.
